Judge Neil Gorsuch began the process of being confirmed as a Justice on the United States Supreme Court by delivering an opening statement before Senators on the Judiciary Committee. The confirmation hearings are expected to last four days, during which Judge Gorsuch will answer questions from Senators and potentially hear testimony from outside witnesses. The week's schedule is as follows: Monday - opening remarks, Tuesday - questions from Senators, Wednesday - more questions from Senators and potentially hearing testimony, Thursday - conclusion of witness testimony.